knowledge in that classroom.

00:56:15.140 --> 00:56:17.160
What I could be is the
person who opens up the door.

00:56:17.160 --> 00:56:20.670
And says, "Here's
questions to ask.

00:56:20.670 --> 00:56:22.240
Here are places to go.

00:56:22.240 --> 00:56:24.970
Here are people who might
have the answers about this.

00:56:24.970 --> 00:56:29.820
Here's how you can find
out what you're doing."

00:56:29.820 --> 00:56:33.810
What is important to
know when you teach

00:56:33.810 --> 00:56:35.970
like that is it's terrifying.

00:56:35.970 --> 00:56:37.810
Right? If you've been
trained to be the professor

00:56:37.810 --> 00:56:41.290
at the front of the classroom.

00:56:41.290 --> 00:56:43.230
You have been taught
in graduate school

00:56:43.230 --> 00:56:44.690
that you are supposed
to be the expert.

00:56:44.690 --> 00:56:46.560
